        "body": "**Missing error handling for uvicorn.run() startup failures**\n\nThe uvicorn.run() call on line 1256 has no try/except block to handle common startup failures. If the port is already in use (OSError: Address already in use), user lacks permission to bind the host, or the server fails to start, uvicorn will raise an unhandled exception with a raw Python traceback instead of a user-friendly error message. This violates basic CLI best practices for error reporting.\n\nRaised by: claude-code\n\nSuggested fix: Add exception handling: `try:\\n    uvicorn.run(server_app, host=host, port=port)\\nexcept OSError as e:\\n    typer.echo(f'error: Failed to start server: {e}', err=True)\\n    raise typer.Exit(1)`",
