        "body": "**Console output will be mixed with uvicorn's logging output**\n\nThe serve() function calls console.print() on line 1255 with Rich markup formatting, then immediately calls uvicorn.run() which has its own logging configuration. This results in two different startup messages with different formats: the Rich-formatted console.print() message and uvicorn's built-in startup logs. In production, this mixing of console output and structured logging can be confusing, especially in containers or CI/CD where log aggregation is needed.\n\nRaised by: claude-code\n\nSuggested fix: Option A (simpler): Remove line 1255 console.print() and rely on uvicorn's built-in logging. Option B: Pass log_config=None to uvicorn.run() to suppress its logging and control it yourself via Python logging. Document the choice in a comment.",
